programme.title: Jurassic Park
programme.desc: On a remote island, a wealthy entrepreneur creates a theme park featuring living dinosaurs drawn from prehistoric DNA. Their park visit is anything but tranquil as the parks security system breaks down, and the prehistoric creatures break out.

programme.title: The Lost World: Jurassic Park
programme.desc: Sequel in which the entrepreneur who genetically engineered the dinosaurs in Jurassic Park transpires to have cloned more of the prehistoric monsters on another island location. programme.title: Jurassic Park III
programme.desc: Dr Alan Grant reluctantly accompanies a rich couple who are searching for their teenage son who crashed on the second Jurassic Park island while paragliding. Unfortunately for the adventurers, there are many unfamiliar - and deadly - dinosaurs lurking in the jungle.

programme.title: Jurassic World
programme.desc: Jurassic Park is now called Jurassic World, a fully functional dinosaur park that sees 20,000 visitors a year, the realisation of owner John Hammonds dreams. The scientists may have gone too far in creating some sort of hybrid dinosaur, which escapes and terrorises the park.

programme.title: Jurassic World: Fallen Kingdom

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.desc: A look back at the extraordinary 1994 final at the Olympic Stadium in Athens between Fabio Capellos AC Milan and Barcelona, managed by Johan Cruyff and dubbed the Dream Team.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.desc: We revisit the 1995 final in Vienna between Louis van Gaals Ajax and AC Milan. A star-studded Ajax team featured Edwin van der Sar, Ronald and Frank de Boer and Edgar Davids.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.desc: We revisit the 1996 final between Ajax and Juventus in Rome. Juves talented side included Didier Deschamps, Antonio Conte and Gianluca Vialli - all at the height of their powers.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.desc: We revisit the 1996/97 UEFA Champions League final between Borussia Dortmund and Juventus in Munich. Armed with an expensively assembled squad, Juve were overwhelming favourites.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.desc: Real Madrid went in search of their seventh European Cup title when they faced Juventus in the 1998 final in Amsterdam. The Serie A winners featured a 25-year-old Zinedine Zidane.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.sub-title: 1998/99 Final: Manchester United v Bayern Munich
programme.desc: We revisit the extraordinary 1998/99 UEFA Champions League final between Manchester United and Bayern Munich at the Nou Camp. Victory for United would clinch an historic Treble.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.desc: A look back at the 1999/00 UEFA Champions League final between Real Madrid and Valencia in Paris. Steve McManaman, signed from Liverpool the previous summer, starred for Madrid.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.desc: We revisit the dramatic 2000/01 UEFA Champions League final between Bayern Munich and Valencia at the San Siro in Milan. Bayern were chasing their first title in a quarter-century.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.sub-title: 2002 Final: Real Madrid v Bayer 04 Leverkusen
programme.desc: The 2001/02 UEFA Champions League final saw a star-studded Real Madrid face Bayer Leverkusen in Glasgow. The match featured arguably the greatest goal in the competitions history.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.desc: We revisit the 2002/03 UEFA Champions League final between Juventus and AC Milan at Old Trafford. Paolo Maldini aimed to lift the trophy as captain, just as his father did in 1963.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.sub-title: 2004 Final: AS Monaco v FC Porto
programme.desc: A look back at the 2004 final between Monaco and Porto in Gelsenkirchen. Porto were led by Jose Mourinho, who would leave the club to take over at Chelsea two days after the final.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.desc: This edition revisits the 2005 UEFA Champions League final which saw Liverpool come back from three goals down, with goals from Gerrard, Smicer and Alonso to beat AC Milan on penalties in Istanbul, Turkey.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.desc: The 2005/06 UEFA Champions League final in Paris saw Arsenal face a pre-Lionel Messi Barcelona, then under the command of Frank Rijkaard, and featuring Ronaldinho in his pomp.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.desc: We rewind back to the 2007 final at the Olympic Stadium in Athens as AC Milan looked to avenge their humiliating defeat two years previously against Rafa Benitezs Liverpool.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.desc: A look back at the 2007/08 UEFA Champions League final between Manchester United and Chelsea at Moscows Luzhniki Stadium, the first all-English final in the competitions history.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.desc: A look back at the 2009 UEFA Champions League final between Barcelona and Man Utd in Rome. United were bidding to become the first team to defend the trophy in the modern era.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.sub-title: 2010 Final: Bayern Munich v Internazionale Milan
programme.desc: We revisit the 2010 UEFA Champions League final between Bayern Munich and Inter Milan at the Bernabeu. Jose Mourinho was looking to become the third man to win it with two clubs.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.desc: The 2010/11 UEFA Champions League final saw Manchester United come up against Pep Guardiolas Barcelona at Wembley, the scene of Uniteds first European Cup success back in 1968.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.desc: We revisit the 2011/12 UEFA Champions League final between Bayern Munich and Chelsea at the Allianz Arena. This was Chelseas second final, having lost their last in 2008.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.sub-title: 2013 Final: Borussia Dortmund v Bayern Munich

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.sub-title: 2013/14 Final: Real Madrid v Atletico Madrid
programme.desc: The 2013/14 UEFA Champions League final in Lisbon saw Real Madrid go head-to-head with arch-rivals Atletico Madrid. Real aimed to become the first club to win the trophy 10 times.

programme.title: UEFA Champions League Classics
programme.desc: We revisit last seasons enthralling UEFA Champions League final between Juventus and Barcelona in Berlin. Barcelona were chasing their third Champions League title in six years.

programme.title: MotoGP Classics
